## Testing Standards

### Test Structure
```go
package config

import "testing"
{% if use_testify %}
import "github.com/stretchr/testify/assert"
{% endif %}

func TestLoad_MissingFileReturnsDefault(t *testing.T) {
	cfg, err := Load("does-not-exist.{{ config_format if has_config_file else 'yaml' }}")
	{% if use_testify %}
	assert.NoError(t, err)
	{% else %}
	if err != nil {
		t.Fatalf("unexpected error: %v", err)
	}
	{% endif %}
}
```

### Test Naming
- Test files: `<file>_test.go`, next to the file under test (Go convention - not a separate `tests/` directory)
- Test functions: `Test<Function>_<Scenario>` (e.g. `TestLoad_MissingFileReturnsDefault`)

### Table-Driven Tests
For functions with several input/output cases, prefer a table-driven test over repeated near-identical test functions:
```go
func TestParseLogLevel(t *testing.T) {
	cases := []struct {
		input string
		want  slog.Level
	}{
		{"debug", slog.LevelDebug},
		{"warn", slog.LevelWarn},
		{"unknown", slog.LevelInfo},
	}
	for _, c := range cases {
		if got := parseLogLevel(c.input); got != c.want {
			t.Errorf("parseLogLevel(%q) = %v, want %v", c.input, got, c.want)
		}
	}
}
```
